Well when you are manic (the high) its pure euphoria its like youve taken ecstasy that doesnt wear off. You are energised happy you feel like you could do anything you might notice she is more sexual, pressured speech. But there arent upsides without the downsides, spending money like crazy, impulsivity risky behaviour. The best you can do for her is :
1. Take her to her doctor and get her on her medication immediately
2. Be there for her (this one is really exhausting i know but she cant be alone and back to point one thats why she needs to go on medication because you cant only sleep for 3 hours like her it would exhaust you.)
Depression however same steps but try to get her to do at least two tasks a day! Brush her teeth, wash her hair. Try to make her do stuff. Dont force it but try. I hope ive been a little but of help.
